Vice President Mike Pence addressed the 161st session of the Southern Baptist Convention in Dallas, Texas. He brought greetings from President Donald Trump and expressed his admiration for the Southern Baptist Convention. Pence highlighted the impact of the convention's churches, which minister to over 15 million people in all 50 states. He praised the convention's commitment to spreading the message of Christ and its efforts to bring about renewal and new beginnings in America. Pence also discussed the progress made by the Trump administration, including rebuilding the military, securing the borders, and standing up to terrorism. He emphasized the administration's commitment to protecting religious liberty, appointing conservative judges, and supporting persecuted Christians. Pence concluded by urging the convention to continue its important work and to pray for America's future.